headline: Analog Devices Dividend Hike Highlights AI Growth And Valuation Tension
summary: Analog Devices (NasdaqGS:ADI) announced an 11% increase in its quarterly dividend, extending a track record of more than 20 years of annual dividend growth. The company reported earnings growth alongside a recovery across multiple end markets. Management highlighted AI data center opportunities and industrial demand as key drivers. Analog Devices, trading around $355.15, has recently posted share price gains, with the stock up 5.4% over the past week and 16.2% over the past month. Returns...
